The Dual Thrust trading algorithm is a famous strategy developed by Michael Chalek. Its logical prototype is one of the most common Day trading strategies. The opening range breakout strategy is based on today’s opening price plus or minus a certain percentage of yesterday’s amplitude to determine the upper and lower rails. When the price breaks through the upper track, it will buy long, and when it breaks the lower track, it will sell short.

When using this strategy, on the one hand, you can refer to the optimal parameters of historical data testing. On the other hand, you can start to adjust K1 and K2 in stages according to your own judgment of the post-trend or from other major cycle technical indicators.
